-- Four Miners Feared Dead in Coal India’s Jharkhand Mine Accident
-- B y   U n n i   K r i s h n a n   a n d   R a j e s h   K u m a r   S i n g h
-- 2013-11-11T12:24:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-11/four-miners-feared-dead-in-coal-india-s-jharkhand-mine-accident.html
Four workers are feared dead after
the ceiling of an underground mine of  Coal India Ltd. (COAL)  collapsed
today in the eastern state of Jharkhand.  One of the bodies has been recovered, said Prashant Kumar,
deputy commissioner of Dhanbad district, where the Basantimata
mine is located. Efforts to recover the remaining bodies are on
and work has been halted at the mine, which produces 300 metric
tons daily, said T.K. Lahiry, chairman of unit Bharat Coking
Coal Ltd.  Coal  India  reported 56 mining deaths in 2012, compared with
51 the previous year, according to its annual report. Production
from underground mines was about 8 percent of the total in the
quarter ended June 30, according to the company’s website.  The company will employ one member of the family of the
deceased and give monetary compensation, Lahiry said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
